<br>
'Yes, you can say hello. I rarely get any visitors here and I thought perhaps there was trouble abroad. Well in any case I am grateful for your company. My wife is gone I suppose, to where I have no idea. She goes out and about as she pleases and I have not seen her for a long while.<br>
<br>
     As for my adventures I have traveled far and wide to the lands of the east. I've had social contacts with other gods in the lands about Asia. They are a diverse group, their numbers far outstrip us though I daresay their power is lacking compared to the original Olympian Gods, which includes myself. <br>
<br>
     As for you, you are a sight to behold in this somewhat bleek realm of mine. Love the hair and your outfit is stunning.'<br>
<br>
::He beams a smile at her.::<br>
<br>
'So tell me, how have things been for you?' <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/20/01 4:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: His Return</span><hr size=1> pops the last cherry in her mouth before making the bag disappear.<br>
