<br>
'I can understand your displeasure. I do not get along with the amazons myself. Perhaps I am the most hated god amongst them. You would think people would show gratitude to you if you promised them your protection and even give them gifts, though they themselves are not worthy of recieving them. They harbored suspicious and angry thoughts about me. There were others who even threatened me with physical conflict if they were to see me in their lands again.'<br>
<br>
::Waves his right hand as if dismissing someone.::<br>
<br>
'Well to Hades with them and a punishment just for their mistreatment of me. Anyways I think the new look is good Hecate. I find no need myself for all those clothes except when going into battle with my battle armour.'<br>
<br>
   'So tell me if you will what has been going on in mortal  lands. I would like to know that very much.'  <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(9/21/01 1:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: His Return</span><hr size=1> pulling a small cobra from her hair she holds him i front of her and kisses it while looking up to Poseidon<br>
